# .trivyignore — Accepted risk exceptions
# Format: CVE-ID  # reason | expires: YYYY-MM-DD | owner: @handle
#
# Every entry MUST have a reason, expiry, and owner.
# Expired entries will cause the pipeline to fail — this is intentional.
# Review process: open a PR to renew or remove entries.

# Example (remove before production use):
# CVE-2023-XXXXX  # false positive in test dependency only, not in final image | expires: 2026-07-01 | owner: @your-handle
